c0b0699a.png%252F930x520.png?signature=Ym6QRZFT9GiLrr6OqHDs2RRYf3s=&source=https%3A%2F%2Fblueprint-api-production.s3.amazonaws.com\",\"mediaid\":\"kEoDrPxAnp\",\"preload\":false,\"title\":\"How to recognize and avoid fake news\",\"sources\":[{\"file\":\"https://vdist.aws.mashable.com/cms/2020/7/c57eeef4-da2a-0ad1/hls.m3u8\"},{\"file\":\"https://vdist.aws.mashable.com/cms/2020/7/c57eeef4-da2a-0ad1/dash.mpd\"},{\"file\":\"https://vdist.aws.mashable.com/cms/2020/7/c57eeef4-da2a-0ad1/mp4/1080.mp4\"},{\"file\":\"https://vdist.aws.mashable.com/cms/2020/7/c57eeef4-da2a-0ad1/mp4/720.mp4\"},{\"file\":\"https://vdist.aws.mashable.com/cms/2020/7/c57eeef4-da2a-0ad1/mp4/480.mp4\"}],\"player_id\":\"WmgvXppl\"},\"options\":{\"disableAds\":false,\"disableSharing\":false,\"nextupAction\":\"autoplay\",\"embedUrl\":\"https://mashable.com/videos/blueprint:kEoDrPxAnp/embed/?player=offsite\",\"standaloneUrl\":null,\"post\":{\"url\":\"https://mashable.com/article/qanon-conspiracy-baby-boomers-4chan/\",\"date\":\"2018-08-07T14:47:48.974Z\",\"bp_id\":78758,\"wp_id\":null}},\"advertising\":{\"params\":{\"keywords\":\"mashable-video,culture,trump,fake news,fact check\",\"sec0\":null,\"sec1\":\"\",\"prc\":\"\"}},\"analytics\":{\"labels\":\"mashable-video,culture,trump,fake news,fact check\",\"videoSeriesName\":null}}Donald Trump has once again incurred the incredibly mild wrath of Twitter.\nAlmost six hours after the President of the United States fired off a lie-filled tweet about the dangers of \"Mail Drop Boxes\" for election ballots, the Twitter Safety team took notice. Rather than remove the tweet, Twitter will allow it to stand with some restrictions and a notice about how it violates the site's policies.\nWe placed a public interest notice on this Tweet for violating our Civic Integrity Policy for making misleading health claims that could potentially dissuade people from participation in voting. https://t.co/MA6E7mBpkmâ€” Twitter Safety (@TwitterSafety) August 23, 2020\n\nA follow-up tweet from Twitter Safety notes that the original tweet will be allowed to live on, just with limited engagements. That means no likes, no replies, and re-tweets without comment. It won't be deleted because most Trump tweets are considered relevant \"to ongoing public conversation\" by definition.\nSo now, anyone who looks at the newly flagged tweet will see a message sitting between it and the president's account info:\n\"This Tweet violated the Twitter Rules about civic and election integrity. However, Twitter has determined that it may be in the public's interest for the Tweet to remain accessible,\" the message reads, daring us not to laugh ruefully.\nWe're almost four years into this presidency and many have come to view Trump as a walking, talking, rage-filled manifestation of the \"old man yells at cloud\" meme. U.S. president or not, maybe it's time to re-think the old public interest rules. Eh, Twitter?\nThe company has taken an increasingly firm stance on Trump's social media behavior, which is to say multiple tweets emanating from the president's account have been flagged, but not removed, since May 2020. The latest flag marks the second time in recent months that Trump's dishonest portrayal of U.S. elections specifically has drawn Twitter's (again, incredibly mild) wrath."},"image":"https://mondrian.mashable.com/uploads%252Fstory%252Fthumbnail%252F118463%252Fdbab8b5c-6aeb-4bb2-8094-8cdb09e37235.jpg%252F950x534__filters%253Aquality%252880%2529.jpg?signature=sCQOm-cdkFZbv5lxveWU9KG5Oxw=&source=https%3A%2F%2Fblueprint-api-production.s3.amazonaws.com","feature_image":"https://mondrian.mashable.com/uploads%252Fstory%252Fthumbnail%252F118463%252Fdbab8b5c-6aeb-4bb2-8094-8cdb09e37235.jpg%252F1438x0.jpg?signature=B5-kT-gp7Vh9s74TPEcR-rTihlU=&source=https%3A%2F%2Fblueprint-api-production.s3.amazonaws.com","responsive_images":[{"image":"https://mondrian.mashable.com/uploads%252Fstory%252Fthumbnail%252F118463%252Fdbab8b5c-6aeb-4bb2-8094-8cdb09e37235.jpg%252F280x158.jpg?signature=vjl6SFSFTBeY-EAcw1ONhFYRUKM=&source=https%3A%2F%2Fblueprint-api-production.s3.amazonaws.com","query":true,"size":"280x158#"},{"image":"https://mondrian.mashable.com/uploads%252Fstory%252Fthumbnail%252F118463%252Fdbab8b5c-6aeb-4bb2-8094-8cdb09e37235.jpg%252F560x316.jpg?signature=a2puhJYQzH3N5M7UmMjGsMlhG7M=&source=https%3A%2F%2Fblueprint-api-production.s3.amazonaws.com","query":"(min-resolution: 1.5dppx)","size":"560x316#"}],"responsive_images_html5":{"img_set_info":{"tag_attributes":{"alt":"Hey look, it's a day ending in 'y'! Time for Twitter to flag another lying Trump tweet.","src":"https://mondrian.mashable.com/uploads%252Fstory%252Fthumbnail%252F118463%252Fdbab8b5c-6aeb-4bb2-8094-8cdb09e37235.jpg%252F280x158.jpg?signature=vjl6SFSFTBeY-EAcw1ONhFYRUKM=\u0026source=https%3A%2F%2Fblueprint-api-production.s3.amazonaws.com","src_type":"jpg","loading":"lazy","version_webp_srcset":"https://mondrian.mashable.com/uploads%252Fstory%252Fthumbnail%252F118463%252Fdbab8b5c-6aeb-4bb2-8094-8cdb09e37235.webp%252F280x158.webp?signature=kexmr_XBQYTXBXEjHti5tMXU_hE=\u0026source=https%3A%2F%2Fblueprint-api-production.s3.amazonaws.com 280w","naturalWidth":"280","srcset":"https://mondrian.mashable.com/uploads%252Fstory%252Fthumbnail%252F118463%252Fdbab8b5c-6aeb-4bb2-8094-8cdb09e37235.jpg%252F280x158.jpg?signature=vjl6SFSFTBeY-EAcw1ONhFYRUKM=\u0026source=https%3A%2F%2Fblueprint-api-production.s3.amazonaws.com 280w","sizes":"280w"}},"image_caption_info":null,"image_credit_info":null,"data_clickthrough_info":null,"version_webp_callback":{}},"display_title":"Hey look, it's a day ending in 'y'! Time for Twitter to flag another lying Trump tweet.","choice":false,"mash_debut":false,"weed_in_america":false,"spotlight":false,"shortcode_data":{"gallery":[],"giftguide":{}},"excerpt":"Donald Trump has once again incurred the incredibly mild wrath of Twitter.","show_sponsorship":null,"sponsorship_footer":null,"channel":"Tech","channel_label":"Tech","channel_link":"https://mashable.com/Tech/","tweet_text":"Hey look, it's a day ending in 'y'! Time for Twitter to flag another lying Trump tweet."}]
  window.__bootstrap = {"topic":{"_id":"4d2f9cc15198403967000008","id":"tech","name":"Tech","posts_count":64538,"url":"https://mashable.com/category/tech/","responsive_images":null,"responsive_images_html5":{"img_set_info":{"tag_attributes":{"alt":null,"src_type":"jpeg","loading":"lazy","srcset":"https://mondrian.mashable.com/2012%252F12%252F04%252F83%252Ftechnology.57Y%252F950x534.57Y?signature=TkAjm-qzkUwwDiTw_TVshaQebxI= 950w","sizes":" 950w"}},"image_caption_info":null,"image_credit_info":null,"data_clickthrough_info":null,"version_webp_callback":null}},"data":[{"_id":"5f4d9e6999fe6f0054000002","id":"/article/twitter-quote-retweets-with-comments/","title":"Twitter's 'Quote Tweet' changes make sussing out online drama easier","title_tag":null,"author":"Amanda Yeo","post_date":"2020-09-01T01:05:42+00:00","post_date_rfc":"Tue, 01 Sep 2020 01:05:42 +0000","formatted_date":" 1 hour ago","sort_key":"1KcUK2","link":"https://mashable.com/article/twitter-quote-retweets-with-comments/","content":{"plain":"Twitter's incredibly handy \"Retweets with comments\" feature is getting a rebranding, as well as becoming a tiny bit more convenient to use.\nEarlier this year, Twitter added the option to see retweets that include a comment without having to use an automated account such as @QuotedReplies. Now the feature has been renamed, ditching the descriptive but clunky \"Retweets with comments\" for the cleaner \"Quote Tweets.\"Â \nQuote Tweets also appear between the Retweets and Likes on a tweet now, making the feature slightly less annoying to access. Previously, you had to click to see the Retweets, then click \"Retweets with comments\" from there. Now, you can just jump straight to the drama.\nThe update is live, with the official Twitter account announcing the changes on Monday. Also: \"The mask goes over your nose.\"\nThree thingsâ€”1. \"Retweets with comments\" is changing to \"Quote Tweets\"2. Quote Tweets will appear right next to Retweets3. The mask goes over your nose pic.twitter.com/x00YTZSAFsâ€” Twitter (@Twitter) August 31, 2020\n\nSEE ALSO: Twitter is testing a feature that will let you see quote retweets\nTwitter's changes to \"Retweets with comments\" do a little to streamline the feature, which is appreciated. But the bigger value is in how much easier it now is to see if someone's being ratioed at a glance.\nMore retweets than comments? Congrats on going viral. More quote retweets? Brace yourself."},"image":"https://mondrian.mashable.com/uploads%252Fcard%252Fimage%252F1476781%252Fa174beae-546c-49de-82d4-bed4098e6568.jpg%252F950x534__filters%253Aquality%252880%2529.jpg?signature=Zp1r9kQ7cosYccxKjWbA3fiTCeI=&source=https%3A%2F%2Fblueprint-api-production.s3.amazonaws.com","feature_image":"https://mondrian.mashable.com/uploads%252Fstory%252Fthumbnail%252F118755%252F327cba65-3333-4723-b3bf-6d8a599cf1ec.jpg%252F1438x0.jpg?signature=ux9D7PKu0ZR3BUl-EmcR8hTzvx0=&source=https%3A%2F%2Fblueprint-api-production.s3.amazonaws.com","responsive_images":[{"image":"https://mondrian.mashable.com/uploads%252Fstory%252Fthumbnail%252F118755%252F327cba65-3333-4723-b3bf-6d8a599cf1ec.jpg%252F356x205.jpg?signature=Ly81AT6KXAH6y5p2GEvCswWbtbc=&source=https%3A%2F%2Fblueprint-api-production.s3.amazonaws.com","query":true,"size":"356x205#"},{"image":"https://mondrian.mashable.com/uploads%252Fstory%252Fthumbnail%252F118755%252F327cba65-3333-4723-b3bf-6d8a599cf1ec.jpg%252F712x410.jpg?signature=MAYYSbLqPtFrPieKyo4l67A0_4k=&source=https%3A%2F%2Fblueprint-api-production.s3.amazonaws.com","query":"(min-resolution: 1.5dppx)","size":"712x410#"},{"image":"https://mondrian.mashable.com/uploads%252Fstory%252Fthumbnail%252F118755%252F327cba65-3333-4723-b3bf-6d8a599cf1ec.jpg%252F280x157.jpg?signature=et_rKGqcNC93Uv9xRlK9KE7RySg=&source=https%3A%2F%2Fblueprint-api-production.s3.amazonaws.com","query":"(max-width: 480px)","size":"280x157#"},{"image":"https://mondrian.mashable.com/uploads%252Fstory%252Fthumbnail%252F118755%252F327cba65-3333-4723-b3bf-6d8a599cf1ec.jpg%252F560x314.jpg?signature=kC0fbown49BiCjEwXjukxewSobY=&source=https%3A%2F%2Fblueprint-api-production.s3.amazonaws.com","query":"(max-width: 480px) and (min-resolution: 1.5dppx)","size":"560x314#"}],"responsive_images_html5":{"img_set_info":{"tag_attributes":{"class":"microcontent","alt":"Twitter is making a few tiny changes to how you see retweets with comments.","src":"https://mondrian.mashable.com/lead-img-twitter-quote-retweets-with-comments.jpg","data":{"fragment":"lead-image","url":null,"image":"https://mondrian.mashable.com/lead-img-twitter-quote-retweets-with-comments.jpg","micro":1},"src_type":"jpg","loading":"lazy","naturalWidth":"356","srcset":"https://mondrian.mashable.com/uploads%252Fcard%252Fimage%252F1476781%252Fa174beae-546c-49de-82d4-bed4098e6568.jpg%252F280x157__filters%253Aquality%252880%2529.jpg?signature=kLMIyTakc41PVWxeriK7hdNzBkE=\u0026source=https%3A%2F%2Fblueprint-api-production.s3.amazonaws.com 280w,https://mondrian.mashable.com/uploads%252Fcard%252Fimage%252F1476781%252Fa174beae-546c-49de-82d4-bed4098e6568.jpg%252F356x205__filters%253Aquality%252880%2529.jpg?signature=3VrapcQ7WphqAGyjWNuB-dvRopo=\u0026source=https%3A%2F%2Fblueprint-api-production.s3.amazonaws.com 356w","sizes":"(max-width: 480px) 280w,356w"}},"image_caption_info":{"tag_attributes":{"class":"image-caption","content":"Twitter is making a few tiny changes to how you see retweets with comments."}},"image_credit_info":{"tag_attributes":{"class":"image-credit","content":"Image:  Aytac Unal / Anadolu Agency / Getty Images"}},"data_clickthrough_info":null,"version_webp_callback":{}},"display_title":"Twitter's 'Quote Tweet' changes make sussing out online drama easier","choice":false,"mash_debut":false,"weed_in_america":false,"spotlight":false,"shortcode_data":{"gallery":[],"giftguide":{}},"excerpt":"More retweets than comments? Congrats on going viral. More quote retweets? Brace yourself.","show_sponsorship":null,"sponsorship_footer":null,"channel":"Tech","channel_label":"Tech","channel_link":"https://mashable.com/Tech/","tweet_text":"Twitter's 'Quote Tweet' changes make sussing out online drama easier"},{"_id":"5f4d9a63146e6f005d000009","id":"/article/tik-tok-commerce-teespring/","title":"TikTok's new commerce integration lets creators start milkin' content for cash","title_tag":null,"author":"Rachel Kraus","post_date":"2020-09-01T00:48:32+00:00","post_date_rfc":"Tue, 01 Sep 2020 00:48:32 +0000","formatted_date":" 2 hours ago","sort_key":"1KcUtq","link":"https://mashable.com/article/tik-tok-commerce-teespring/","content":{"plain":"TikTok is making it easier for creators to turn looped video streams into pure American profit.Â \nThe embattled social media company announced Monday that it had entered into a new partnership with the customized online merch platform Teespring. The integration will allow creators to include links to their Teespring products directly in their videos.\nTikTokkers with hearty followings already frequently link to personal merchandise stores in their bios. Selling merch like clothing, as well as digital tutorials or templates, is a popular way for independent creators to earn cash from the people who consume their content for free. The new Teespring integration builds on what creators are already doing themselves with an official and more streamlined tool.\n\"Creators are the heart and soul of TikTok and we are constantly looking for ways to bring more value and opportunities for them within our platform,\" Sean Kim, TikTok's US head of product, told Mashable in an emailed statement. \"Teespring empowers creators to design and sell their own products, and this shared creator-first mindset made them the right partner for an e-commerce integration. We are looking forward to building upon our ongoing commitment to support creators through monetary opportunities and, in the meantime, are excited to see what ideas creators bring to life on Teespring.\"\nThe program is currently in beta testing, and will officially launch in September. Teespring is already working with 7,000+ creators and has invited some of them into a private beta. Creators who want to get the integration will have to meet eligibility criteria around the amount of followers they have and the content they produce.\nYou can see an example of what the new integration will look like through this post from TikTok user @bonnierzm: If you open the link in the TikTok app, a translucent gray box with a shopping bag icon with the words \"Limited edition shirt here\" appears, linked to BonnieRZM's Teespring store. As opposed to a Teespring link in bio, which takes users out of the app and to an external web page, clicking on the in-video link opens the store within TikTok itself.Â \n\nHaving shopping all in one place is a valuable tool for creators trying to sell products, because the fewer steps there are between your social media page and the \"buy\" â€” less friction in sales speak â€” the more it encourages people to make that purchase. That's something Facebook knows well, as it continues to make shopping in Instagram ever more integrated with the experience.\nWhat's not clear yet is what's in it for TikTok. The company has launched several initiatives to help its creators make money, including a $1 billion TikTok Creator Fund that it will allocate to users for their businesses over the next three years. However, TikTok and Teespring declined to answer whether the companies would make commissions on sales made through the integration. Teespring makes its money by actually providing and selling the products (whether physical or digital) to the owners of the customized stores. But what piece of the pie TikTok will get remains to be seen."},"image":"https://mondrian.mashable.com/uploads%252Fcard%252Fimage%252F1476768%252F4fb50d73-5baa-4358-a6ad-8eded81626a1.jpg%252F950x534__filters%253Aquality%252880%2529.jpg?signature=Al5fQfQc0tUrpj-hegbI_btptIQ=&source=https%3A%2F%2Fblueprint-api-production.s3.amazonaws.com","feature_im